Preheat oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.Place the haddock fillet onto a baking sheet and spread the mustard over the fish.In a mini food processor, blend together the breadcrumbs, Stilton, parsley and 15g/Â½oz of butter and press onto the fish.Transfer the baking sheet to the oven and cook for 8-10 minutes, or until golden-brown and cooked through.Place the rest of the butter, along with the dill and lemon juice into a small saucepan and heat over a low heat until the butter has melted, then season well with salt and freshly ground black pepper.To serve, place the fish onto a serving plate, with lemon wedges alongside, and pour the sauce over the fish.